                      <p id="fs-idp36624368">
                        In this equation,
                        <em data-effect="italics">h</em> is Planck’s constant and
                        <em data-effect="italics">
                          E
                          <sub>i</sub>
                        </em> and
                        <em data-effect="italics">
                          E
                          <sub>f</sub>
                        </em> are the initial and final orbital energies, respectively. The absolute value of the energy difference is used, since frequencies and wavelengths are always positive. Instead of allowing for continuous values of energy, Bohr assumed the energies of these electron orbitals were quantized:
                      </p>

