                        <p id="fs-idp89066240">
                          <span
                            data-type="title"
                          >Calculating the Energy of an Electron in a Bohr Orbit</span>
                          Early researchers were very excited when they were able to predict the energy of an electron at a particular distance from the nucleus in a hydrogen atom. If a spark promotes the electron in a hydrogen atom into an orbit with
                          <em data-effect="italics">n</em> = 3, what is the calculated energy, in joules, of the electron?
                        </p>
                        <p id="fs-idp40593920">
                          <span data-type="title">Solution</span>
                          The energy of the electron is given by this equation:
                        </p>
                        <div data-type="equation" id="fs-idp20573264">
                          <math display="block">
                            <semantics>
                              <mrow>
                                <mrow>
                                  <mi>E</mi>
                                  <mo>=</mo>
