                      <div data-type="example" id="fs-idp30549440">
                        <h3 class="os-title">
                          <span class="os-title-label">Example</span>
                          <span class="os-number">6.5</span>
                          <span class="os-divider"></span>
                        </h3>
                        <p id="fs-idp19229392">
                          <span
                            data-type="title"
                          >Calculating the Energy and Wavelength of Electron Transitions in a One–electron (Bohr) System</span>
                          What is the energy (in joules) and the wavelength (in meters) of the line in the spectrum of hydrogen that represents the movement of an electron from Bohr orbit with
                          <em data-effect="italics">n</em> = 4 to the orbit with
                          <em data-effect="italics">n</em> = 6? In what part of the electromagnetic spectrum do we find this radiation?
                        </p>
                        <p id="fs-idp19670528">
                          <span data-type="title">Solution</span>
                          In this case, the electron starts out with
                          <em data-effect="italics">n</em> = 4, so
                          <em data-effect="italics">n</em>
                          <sub>1</sub> = 4. It comes to rest in the
                          <em data-effect="italics">n</em> = 6 orbit, so
                          <em data-effect="italics">n</em>
                          <sub>2</sub> = 6. The difference in energy between the two states is given by this expression:
                        </p>
                        <div data-type="equation" id="fs-idp12132608">
                          <math display="block">
                            <semantics>
                              <mrow>
                                <mrow>
                                  <mtext>Δ</mtext>
                                  <mi>E</mi>
                                  <mo>=</mo>
                                  <msub>
                                    <mi>E</mi>
                                    <mn>1</mn>
                                  </msub>
                                  <mo>−</mo>
                                  <msub>
                                    <mi>E</mi>
                                    <mn>2</mn>
                                  </msub>
                                  <mo>=</mo>
                                  <mn>2.179</mn>
                                  <mspace width="0.2em"/>
                                  <mo>×</mo>
                                  <mspace width="0.2em"/>
                                  <msup>
                                    <mrow>
                                      <mn>10</mn>
                                    </mrow>
                                    <mrow>
                                      <mn>−18</mn>
                                    </mrow>
                                  </msup>
                                  <mrow>
                                    <mo>(</mo>
                                    <mrow>
                                      <mspace width="0.2em"/>
                                      <mfrac>
                                        <mn>1</mn>
                                        <mrow>
                                          <msubsup>
                                            <mi>n</mi>
                                            <mn>1</mn>
                                            <mn>2</mn>
                                          </msubsup>
                                        </mrow>
                                      </mfrac>
                                      <mspace width="0.2em"/>
                                      <mo>−</mo>
                                      <mspace width="0.2em"/>
                                      <mfrac>
                                        <mn>1</mn>
                                        <mrow>
                                          <msubsup>
                                            <mi>n</mi>
                                            <mn>2</mn>
                                            <mn>2</mn>
                                          </msubsup>
                                        </mrow>
                                      </mfrac>
                                      <mspace width="0.2em"/>
                                    </mrow>
                                    <mo>)</mo>
                                  </mrow>
                                </mrow>
                              </mrow>
                              <annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content">
                                <mrow>
                                  <mtext>Δ</mtext>
                                  <mi>E</mi>
                                  <mo>=</mo>
                                  <msub>
                                    <mi>E</mi>
                                    <mn>1</mn>
                                  </msub>
                                  <mo>−</mo>
                                  <msub>
                                    <mi>E</mi>
